1. d4 { This game, some have dubbed Anand's immortal. A lot of commentators, including Anand himself, compared it to Rubinstein's immortal game as well - inserted as the next chapter in this study purely for reference. } 1... d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 Nbd7 { [%cal Gf1d3] } 6. Bd3 dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 8. Bd3 Bd6 { [%cal Gf8d6] } 9. O-O (9. e4?! e5 $10) 9... O-O 10. Qc2 { [%csl Gh7] } 10... Bb7 { [%cal Gb5b4,Gc3a4,Gc6c5] } 11. a3 { [%csl Gb5][%cal Ga7a6,Gc6c5,Gc3b5,Gd3b5] } 11... Rc8 12. Ng5 { [%cal Gf3g5] } 12... c5 13. Nxh7 { [%cal Gg5h7] } (13. Bxh7+ Kh8) 13... Ng4 { [%cal Gd6h2,Gg4h2] } 14. f4 (14. Nxf8 Bxh2+ 15. Kh1 Qh4 $19) (14. h3 Bh2+ 15. Kh1 Qh4 { [%cal Gh3g4] }) 14... cxd4 { [%csl Gb5,Gh7] } 15. exd4 Bc5!! { [%csl Gd3][%cal Gd7c5,Gd8d3] } 16. Be2 { [%csl Gc5,Gg4] } (16. dxc5 Nxc5 { [%csl Gd3] } 17. Bxb5 Qd4+ 18. Kh1 Ne4 $19 { [%cal Ge4f2,Gg4f2,Gc8c2] } 19. h3 Ng3#) 16... Nde5!! { [%cal Gd8d4,Gd4e5,Gf4e5] } 17. Bxg4 Bxd4+ 18. Kh1 Nxg4 19. Nxf8 { [%cal Gg8f8,Gc2h7] } 19... f5!! { [%cal Gd8h4] } (19... Qh4? 20. Qh7+ { [%cal Gf8h7] } 20... Qxh7 21. Nxh7 Kxh7) 20. Ng6 (20. Nxe6 Qh4 { [%cal Gh4h2] } 21. h3 Qxh3# (21... Qg3 { [%cal Gg3h2] })) 20... Qf6 { [%cal Gf6g6,Gg6h5,Gd4e3] } 21. h3 Qxg6 { [%cal Gh3g4] } 22. Qe2 (22. hxg4 Qh6# { [%cal Gh6h1,Gd4g1,Gb7h1] }) 22... Qh5 { [%cal Gh5h3,Gb7h1] } 23. Qd3 Be3 { 0-1 White resigns. } 24. Bxe3 (24. Qxe3 Nxe3 25. Kg1 Nxf1) (24. Rf3 Bxf3 { [%cal Gh5h3] } 25. gxf3 Qxh3#) 24... Qxh3+ 25. Kg1 Qxg2# 0-1


